Package us.mattgreen

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Talkable
    Talkable:
    Interface for talk and getName Strings.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnimalIO
    AnimalIO:
    This class will prompt the user if they want to enter data for a dog or a cat, then uses createCat or createDog methods to gather the data needed for the Dog or Cat class constructors.
    Cat
    Cat:
    This class is used to instantiate a Cat object, with int attribute of mousesKilled, and String attribute of name.
    Dog
    Dog:
    This class is used to instantiate a Dog object, with boolean attribute of friendly, and String attribute of name.
    FileInput
    FileInput:
    This class attempts to open, read from, and close a file given the file name String provided.
    FileOutput
    FileOutput:
    This class attempts to open, write to, and close a file for output, using given file name String.
    Created by mgreen14 on 12/27/17.
    Main
    Main:
    Instantiates arraylist zoo to hold talkable objects, then uses AnimalIO class methods to prompt user for data to be used in zoo.
    Person
    Person:
    Class for use in instantiating a Person object.
    Pet
    Pet:
    Class for instantiating a Pet object, has name String attribute.
    Student
    Student:
    This class extends Person and implements Talkable.
